Class AntFakeCommunicator

  • java.lang.Object
    • basis.TCPClientCommunicator
      • basis.FakeCommunicator
        • ants.AntFakeCommunicator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable

    public class AntFakeCommunicator
extends FakeCommunicator
    This class represents a fake communicator that aims to play with a bot in training mode. Messages are not sent over the network. The communicator immediately handles game state messages.
    Author:
    JMN

      • setBot

        public void setBot(Bot bot)
        Sets the bot of the fake communicator. The bot constructor requires a communicator so this method is provided to set the bot of the fake communicator after it has been created. { @code AntFakeCommunicator fakeCom = new AntFakeCommunicator(...); Bot fakeBot = new Bot(fakeCom, ...); fakeCom.setBot(fakeBot); }
        Parameters:
        bot - the bot controlled by the communicator.
